			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				It's really quite simple.<BR>
<BR>
If you're level 10, you don't go into the Hole and try to gather loot/experience.  You accept at low levels that there are things in the game that you can't do until you get bigger.  If you do want Hole loot, you either buy it or get high level people to get it for you.<BR>
<BR>
All the trivial loot code does is reverse that statement.  Just as it's true that at level 10 there are things you can't personally camp to get, there are now things that at level 60 you can't personally camp and get.  This code merely removes the one-sided bias of the issue.<BR>
<BR>
Since there is going to be adaptations for quest items, there's absolutely nothing to complain about.
				</font>
