	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				This subject has stirred up a bit of thought. Let me remind myself here what it was like.<BR>
<BR>
First 10 levels: I never had a platnium peice I didn't spend right away. I wanted armor, I wanted to make arrows. I saw people running around with amazing gear, looked up stuff I would one day want on everlore.com and PCed it... only to find out I would never afford it.<BR>
<BR>
10-20: Some of the hardest levels I played were here.I insisted on soloing, and I did. It got a bit boring, but oh well. I finally made more than 200pp at one point in time. I looted some interesting stuff, mothing major until I finally got a DRT from Crush. I was so proud of my first earner armor =)<BR>
<BR>
20-30: People seemed to hate rangers for groups, getting a group was next to impossible (not now though hehe). Solo again. I would get these giant weapons in WW that sold for bucco bux. 950pp. I decided to take a shortcut and buy my Ivy leggings.<BR>
<BR>
30-40: I felt bad about buying my leggings. So I quested. My guild broke up so I had to do most of this myself. It wasn't easy. Took me two months, and I still haven't finished the gloves. That 950pp? That was the highest my bank ever rose to. You see, questing also costs cash. Lots of cash. I believe buying the sleeves actually saved me money.<BR>
<BR>
Here I am at level 42. I have 650pp, almost full Ivy, a Yak and Morin for weapons, a Raincaller I was given in a GM event at level 10 (I felt soooooo uber, at the time it was the best bow) and about to get myself a Fleeting quiver (TYTYTY Verant for giving quivers haste for archery! OMFG this thing rules) and I see people walk around with killer loot. 45 Ranger with a puppy knife. How? Easy. They are in big guilds.<BR>
<BR>
All along I thought I was gonna make tons o' cash in my 30s and 40s. I can't even afford a second yak. I can barely afford to press fletching beyond the 143 it's been at since level 24. There's strength in numbers, and if you're in a big guild you'll get to go on a raid. You'll get some nice loot, eventually.<BR>
<BR>
Then you'll have to sell it. And if there's a lot of other players out there with the same problems as I have, then you're gonna be /auction ing for quite some time.<BR>
<BR>
So are these new loot rules good? If the loot is good for the level, then hell yes. You have to figure lowbies have just as much difficulty scraping together 100pp as a 60 necro does 50kpp for that CoF he or she wants for thier new twink. Making it so the good loot for highbies is impossible to get gives newbies something to show thier friends. Gives them a purpose to group other than mindles leveling that makes this game UNfun.<BR>
<BR>
Besides, you want to farm? Go to Befallen or Runnyeye. There you will find No drop stuff that rivals high level Velious dungeons (robes and talismans at third level, WOW)and beats a lot of high level Kunark stuff too... without the new loot rules =)<BR>
<BR>
Verant has done stuff to please everyone, you just gotta quit complaining and go explore =)<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Tanares the Wind Caller<BR>
42nd Ranger of Tunare<BR>
Luclin (best damn server, no doubt)<BR>

				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
