				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				&quot;The Trivial Loot Code isn't complete and we're continuing to improve it. By the time SoL launches we should be able to mark or flag items such that we can override the Loot Code if we desire. In other words, given that the new looting rules are known by the game designers from the beginning, they are populating the new zones with that code and functionality in mind. And they will have the flexibility to set up quest components and/or other items to use all, part, or none of the new Loot Code.&quot;<BR>
<BR>
I just felt that this quote should be highlighted.<BR>
<BR>
YOU WILL BE ABLE TO DO QUESTS THAT REQUIRE NO DROP ITEMS! THEY WILL MAKE EXCEPTIONS TO THE TLC! YOU WILL NOT BE SHUT OUT OF QUESTS THAT YOU CAN USE TO IMPROVE FACTION!<BR>
<BR>
Now, even an Orc Pawn can understand this, why can't people who have been playing the game for years understand this. <BR>
