	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				I often read the message boards here and I have never commented. But after reading the various posts in this section I had to add my opinion.<BR>
<BR>
I really see nothing wrong with TLC. It prevents higher levels from farming places that lower levels should be enjoying. There are tons of higher level players complaining about this but why? Why do you feel the need for Verant to make it easy for you to loot things from mobs 20 or 30 levels lower than you? That's called exploitation. Did you ever stop and think that the lower level players might deserve a chance to have fun in these zones also? There are tons of zones to support 50+ players, so why not go to those? I can tell you why. Because it means possibly having to kill something that might take a little time and effort. I cannot possibly see why anyone would complain about this- except people who sit and farm all day, and what is the challenge in that? I have a 52 SK and a 41 Necro on Brell and I cannot see myself sitting down in a zone where everything is green and trying to take loot that lower level players should be getting. Farming is ruining the servers and making it difficult for the lower level players to enjoy the game. These people pay $10 a month just like you do, so stop trying to take the enjoyment out of the game. Who wants to be level 1-30 and want to explore a zone in the chances of maybe getting a decent item but you walk in and find a dozen or more 50+ players camping the whole zone then selling the loot for prices that lower levels cannot possibly afford? Where is the fun for them in that? Not everyone who plays EQ is a long time player or a twink. There are new people that subscribe to this game every day, and farmers are robbing them of their chances to enjoy it. Think about it.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
