				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				To respond to some of the comments made previous, things to thing about. <BR>
You see &quot;a monk with a fungi tunic with 2 Kds at level 10&quot; you get upset, why chances r he isnt going to want to loot anything because he has better, and if you group with him then just because he is a twink how does that effect your xp, answer it doesnt. <BR>
Next point lets take the paw of opolar quest. Yes this item is used by people even up to the level of 60 cause of its high WIS. Now add trivial loot code. level 45 comes around the whole quest is green. You cant loot any of the quest bits an excellent quest but because you cant loot the bits you are deprived of it because you didnt do the quest at level 30 because you were getting xp in Over There or Sol B. <BR>
Next thing as quite alot of people have pointed out those who are loyal players to the game and are not new players. We have played for a while we want to have a look around perhaps solve some of the quests the publish the findings on web sites to help other new people. We are unable to do so due to Trivial loot. Also from what I see there is a tried and tested methord of leveling in certain zones. Example. a newbie joins or guild where do i hunt from 20 -25 i gaurntee you for thoes who have played through will say Lake of Ill Omen with out a second thought, as a posed to oooh go to the warrens some great xp there. Or what about 40 - 45 go to Dreads, and why do they say this simple they have tried and tested and found the best places. <BR>
Next point... sorry to rant but this is one of the main points that so many people have forgoten you may be level 10 now but if you become addicted to evercrack like the rest of us you, in 30 levels time YOU will be the ones to say what is all this trivail loot about. Thats the funniest thing of all you are shooting yourselves in the foot and opening your mouths with out looking long term.<BR>
I have to say I have never farmed in a low level dungeon ever but if I found an item that was better than what I was wearing I would go get it, by hook or by crook. If that ment making a level 1 warrior pling him to 20 on another account and sit at a camp and get the item that way then so be it. <BR>
Trivial loot code is not the way forward siple as that. But maybe a level restriction not unlike the procs on weapons may be the answer. Certainly more plausable than a monster who drops somthing doesnt drop it for me cause I am level 60. <BR>
I also see the point that if it is green (concidered &quot;trivial&quot;) then it should not auto attack, play the game from both sides.
